BofA Hires JPMorgan’s Wolff to Co-head Global Corporate Banking

-- B y   H u g h   S o n
-- 
2011-08-03T19:54:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/bofa-hires-jpmorgan-s-wolff-to-co-head-global-corporate-banking.html
Bank of America Corp. (BAC) , the biggest
U.S. bank by assets, hired  JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM) ’s Anne Clarke Wolff to lead global corporate banking operations with Joel Van
Dusen, according to an internal memo.  Wolff, who was head of global sales for Treasury services
at JPMorgan, is expected to join  Charlotte , North Carolina-based
Bank of America in October, according to the memo today from co-
heads of Global Corporate & Investment Banking, Paul Donofrio,
Christian Meissner and Michael Rubinoff. She previously spent
two decades at New York-based Citigroup Inc. in roles including
head of fixed-income capital markets and head of North America
Corporate Banking.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hugh Son in New York at 
 hson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this
